  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Technical Advisor (Marine Engines)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li><p>Provide technical advice and troubleshooting support related to marine engines, propulsion systems, and associated equipment</p></li><li><p>Support pre-sales and post-sales activities with technical input, including specifications, proposals, and solutioning</p></li><li><p>Liaise with clients, shipowners, ship managers, and shipyards on technical matters</p></li><li><p>Review technical documentation, drawings, manuals, and service reports</p></li><li><p>Support commissioning, inspections, maintenance planning, and performance optimisation where required</p></li><li><p>Act as a technical bridge between customers, service teams, and OEMs</p></li><li><p>Keep updated on industry regulations, technical standards, and new technologies</p></li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li><p>Diploma or Degree in Marine Engineering, Mechanical Engineering, or equivalent</p></li><li><p>Sailing experience as a Marine Engineer or shore-based technical experience in shipping/marine engineering</p></li><li><p>Strong knowledge of marine engines and shipboard systems</p></li><li><p>Good communication skills with the ability to explain technical concepts clearly</p></li><li><p>Comfortable working with clients and supporting commercial teams</p></li><li><p>Willingness to travel when required</p></li></ul><p><strong>Preferred</strong></p><ul><li><p>Experience in OEM, ship management, or marine solutions provider environments</p></li><li><p>Prior exposure to advisory, technical support, or customer-facing roles</p></li></ul>",
